quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  22,6,"That is for that Allah -He is The Truth, and that He gives life to the dead and that He is Ever-Determiner over everything"
  22,7,"And for that the Hour is coming up; there is no suspicion about it, and that Allah will make whomever is in the tombs to rise again"
  22,8,And among mankind is he who disputes concerning Allah without knowledge or guidance or an Enlightening Book
  22,9,"Bending his side (i.e., dissuading) to lead into error away from the way of Allah; for him is disgrace in the present (life), (Literally: the lowly \"life\", i.e., the life of this world) and on the Day of the Resurrection We will let him taste the torment of burning"
  22,10,"That is for what your (two) hands have forwarded, and for that Allah is not unjust to (His) bondmen"
  22,11,"And among mankind is he who worships Allah upon the (very) edge; (Literally: as a child) so in case a charitable gain alights upon (i.e., dies) him he is composed therewith, and in case a temptation afflicts him he turns over his face; he loses the present (life) and the Hereafter; that evidently is the greatest loss"
  22,12,"He invokes, apart from Allah, that which does not harm him and which neither profits him (anything); that is the thing that is in far error"
  22,13,He invokes him whose harm is indeed nearer than his proft. Miserable indeed is the patronizer and miserable indeed is the consort
  22,14,Surely Allah will cause the ones who have believed and done deeds of righteousness to enter Gardens from beneath which Rivers run; surely Allah performs whatever He wills
  22,15,"Whoever has (ever) surmised that Allah will never give him victory in the present (life) and the Hereafter, then let him extend forth a means to the heaven, thereafter let him cut it off. Then let him look (for himself): does his plotting definitely put away what enrages him"